comments: O'Neale (UTA) jumps alongside Brunson (DAL) and avoids contact with his arm or body during the driving shot attempt.
Mitchell (UTA) clamps and holds Powell's (DAL) arm, which affects his abiltiy to pursue the rebound.
Powell (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Mitchell (UTA). From all available angles it appears Powell avoids any contact with Mitchell's face/head.
Gobert (UTA) briefly rests a hand on Powell (DAL) and marginal contact occurs before they disengage on the perimeter.
Bogdanovic (UTA) moves alongside of Doncic (DAL) and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the driving shot attempt.
Doncic (DAL) moves alongside of Mitchell (UTA) and marginal contact occurs as they come together, which does not affect Mitchell's SQBR during the drive.
Powell (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
After the pick, Bogdanovic (UTA) and Powell (DAL) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Powell (DAL) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the play at the basket by Mitchell (UTA).
Mitchell (UTA) extends his arms toward Powell (DAL) and makes contact with his face, which affects his ability to contest the play at the basket.
Doncic (DAL) is not vertical when he makes contact with Mitchell's (UTA) arm. which affects Mitchell's shot near the rim.
Gobert (UTA) briefly grasps Finney-Smith's (DAL) jersey and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect Finney-Smith's ability to pursue the rebound.
Mitchell (UTA) moves into and makes contact with Powell's (DAL) body/leg, which affects his SQBR after receiving the pass.
Gobert (UTA) legally contests Dinwiddie's (DAL) jump shot attempt. Dinwiddie extends his leg to create the marginal contact.
